Why not take a holiday to Ghana where you can spend some quality time with your family. We list some family friendly places to visit Cape Coast Castle Cape Coast Castle is one of about forty "slave castles", or large commercial forts, built on the Gold Coast of West Africa by European traders. Today is it one of the biggest historical sites in Ghana. Many tourists come here to learn more about the history and the story behind those here. Aburi Botanical Gardens  Aburi Botanical Gardens is a botanical garden in Aburi in Eastern region of South Ghana. Known as one of the most beautiful botanical garden in Ghana, it occupies an area of 64.8 hectares. The gardens, opened in March, 1890,  is believed to have played an important role in encouraging cocoa production in South Ghana, by supplying cheap cocoa seedlings and information about scientific farming methods. Today one can enjoy the gardens for its picnics  spots or take strolls with loved ones.  Bojo Beach A visit to Ghana is not complete without a visit to Bojo Beach. It is number 6 of 92 spots to visit in the beautiful country.  Why not play a game of beach volleyball or kitesurf while here? Wli waterfall Wli Waterfalls is the highest waterfall in Ghana and West Africa. It is  approximately 280 kilometers from the capital Accra. The pictures says a thousand words… Mole National Park Mole National Park is Ghana's largest wildlife place. In 1971 the small human population of the area was relocated and the lands were designated a national park. Visit here to see an array of wildlife, including some of the big 5 and antelope.